<!-- Energy Audit Section -->

<h2 id="energy-audit-introduction">A. Introduction</h2>
<p>
  This ASHRAE Level II Energy Audit report presents the findings of an energy audit conducted at
  {{project.property_address}}.
  The audit was performed in accordance with ASHRAE standards and includes an analysis of the building's energy usage,
  identification of energy conservation measures, and recommendations for implementation.
</p>

<h2 id="energy-audit-procedures">B. Energy Audit Procedures</h2>
<p>
  The energy audit was conducted using the following procedures:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>On-site facility survey of existing mechanical, electrical, lighting, and control systems</li>
  <li>Interview with operations and maintenance personnel</li>
  <li>Analysis of utility bills and energy usage patterns</li>
  <li>Identification of energy conservation opportunities</li>
  <li>Development of energy conservation measures</li>
  <li>Financial analysis of proposed measures</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="eems-cost-savings-summary-table">C. EEMs Cost Savings Summary Table</h2>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Measure</th>
      <th class="text-right">Annual Savings (kWh)</th>
      <th class="text-right">Cost Savings ($)</th>
      <th class="text-right">Implementation Cost ($)</th>
      <th class="text-right">Payback (years)</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {{#each measures}}
    <tr>
      <td>{{title}}</td>
      <td class="text-right">{{formatNumber estimatedSavings.energy 1}}</td>
      <td class="text-right">{{formatCurrency estimatedSavings.cost}}</td>
      <td class="text-right">{{formatCurrency implementationCost}}</td>
      <td class="text-right">{{formatNumber estimatedSavings.paybackPeriod 1}}</td>
    </tr>
    {{else}}
    <tr>
      <td colspan="5" class="text-center">No energy efficiency measures available</td>
    </tr>
    {{/each}}
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2 id="existing-conditions-observations">D. Existing Conditions and Observations</h2>

<h3 id="general-building-description">1. General Building Description</h3>
<p>
  {{project.description}}
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Building Type:</strong> {{project.building_type}}<br>
  <strong>Year Built:</strong> {{project.property_year_built}}<br>
  <strong>Gross Floor Area:</strong> {{formatNumber project.property_gross_floor_area}} ft²<br>
  <strong>Operating Hours:</strong> {{#if project.operating_hours}}{{project.operating_hours}}{{else}}Monday-Friday:
  8:00 AM - 6:00 PM, Saturday: 9:00 AM - 1:00 PM, Sunday: Closed{{/if}}
</p>

<h3 id="building-envelope">2. Building Envelope</h3>
<p>
  {{#if buildingEnvelope}}{{buildingEnvelope}}{{else}}The building envelope consists of concrete walls with single-pane
  windows. The roof is flat with a built-up roofing system. There are opportunities for improving the building envelope
  through window replacements and additional insulation.{{/if}}
</p>

<h3 id="hvac-control-systems">3. Heating, Ventilation, Air Conditioning (HVAC) and Control Systems</h3>
<p>
  {{#if hvacSystems}}{{hvacSystems}}{{else}}The building is served by a central HVAC system consisting of air handling
  units, chillers, and boilers. The system is controlled by a building automation system (BAS). The equipment is
  original to the building and has reached the end of its useful life. There are opportunities for energy savings
  through equipment upgrades and control system improvements.{{/if}}
</p>

<h3 id="lighting-system-control">4. Lighting System & Control</h3>
<p>
  {{#if lightingSystems}}{{lightingSystems}}{{else}}The building is primarily lit with fluorescent fixtures. The
  lighting is controlled by manual switches with limited occupancy sensors. There are opportunities for energy savings
  through LED upgrades and advanced lighting controls.{{/if}}
</p>

<h3 id="domestic-hot-water">5. Domestic Hot Water</h3>
<p>
  {{#if domesticHotWater}}{{domesticHotWater}}{{else}}Domestic hot water is provided by gas-fired water heaters. The
  system is original to the building and has reached the end of its useful life. There are opportunities for energy
  savings through equipment upgrades and water conservation measures.{{/if}}
</p>

<h3 id="other-equipment">6. Other Equipment</h3>
<p>
  {{#if otherEquipment}}{{otherEquipment}}{{else}}The building has various other equipment including elevators, office
  equipment, and kitchen appliances. There are opportunities for energy savings through equipment upgrades and
  operational improvements.{{/if}}
</p>

<h2 id="energy-efficiency-measures-recommended">E. Energy Efficiency Measures Recommended</h2>

<style>
  /* Metrics boxes for energy efficiency measures */
  .metrics-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    margin: 15px 0 25px 0;
  }

  .metric-box {
    padding: 12px 15px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    min-width: 160px;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .metric-label {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .metric-value {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* Box-specific colors */
  .cost-savings {
    background-color: #ebffee;
  }

  .cost-savings .metric-label {
    color: #006837;
  }

  .energy-savings {
    background-color: #ebf9ff;
  }

  .energy-savings .metric-label {
    color: #005994;
  }

  .payback-period {
    background-color: #f9ebff;
  }

  .payback-period .metric-label {
    color: #8130a7;
  }
</style>

{{#each measures}}
<h3 id="eem-{{@index}}">EEM {{add @index 1}}: {{title}}</h3>
<p>
  <strong>Description:</strong> {{description}}
</p>

<!-- Metrics boxes for key values -->
<div class="metrics-container">
  <div class="metric-box cost-savings">
    <div class="metric-label">Annual Cost Savings</div>
    <div class="metric-value">${{formatNumber estimatedSavings.cost 0}}</div>
  </div>

  <div class="metric-box energy-savings">
    <div class="metric-label">Energy Savings</div>
    <div class="metric-value">{{formatNumber estimatedSavings.energy 0}} kWh/year</div>
  </div>

  <div class="metric-box payback-period">
    <div class="metric-label">Payback Period</div>
    <div class="metric-value">{{formatNumber estimatedSavings.paybackPeriod 1}} years</div>
  </div>
</div>

{{else}}
<p>No energy efficiency measures have been identified at this time.</p>
{{/each}}

<h2 id="eems-already-implemented">F. EEMs Already Implemented</h2>
<p>
  {{#if implementedMeasures}}
  The following energy efficiency measures have already been implemented:
<ul>
  {{#each implementedMeasures}}
  <li>{{this}}</li>
  {{/each}}
</ul>
{{else}}
No energy efficiency measures have been previously implemented.
{{/if}}
</p>

<h2 id="eems-to-consider">G. EEMs to Consider</h2>
{{#if measuresToConsider}}
{{#each measuresToConsider}}
<h3>{{this.title}}</h3>
<p>{{this.description}}</p>
{{/each}}
{{else}}
<p>No additional energy efficiency measures to consider at this time.</p>
{{/if}}

<h2 id="eems-requiring-further-investigation">H. EEMs Requiring Further Investigation</h2>
{{#if measuresForInvestigation}}
{{#each measuresForInvestigation}}
<h3>{{this.title}}</h3>
<p>{{this.description}}</p>
{{/each}}
{{else}}
<p>No energy efficiency measures requiring further investigation at this time.</p>
{{/if}}

<h2 id="energy-star-benchmarking">I. Current ENERGY STAR® Benchmarking Test</h2>
<p>
  {{#if energyStar}}
  The building has an ENERGY STAR score of {{energyStar.score}}. This places the building in the
  {{energyStar.percentile}} percentile compared to similar buildings nationwide.
  {{else}}
  ENERGY STAR benchmarking has not been performed for this building.
  {{/if}}
</p>

<h2 id="energy-use-analysis">J. Energy Use Analysis</h2>

<h3 id="aggregated-electricity">1. Aggregated Electricity</h3>
<p>
  The building's annual electricity consumption is {{formatNumber totalUsage.totalEnergyUsage}} kWh, with an average
  monthly consumption of {{formatNumber monthlyAvgElectricity}} kWh.
</p>

<h3 id="aggregated-natural-gas">2. Aggregated Natural Gas</h3>
<p>
  {{#if totalUsage.naturalGasUsage}}
  The building's annual natural gas consumption is {{formatNumber totalUsage.naturalGasUsage}} therms, with an average
  monthly consumption of {{formatNumber monthlyAvgGas}} therms.
  {{else}}
  The building does not use natural gas.
  {{/if}}
</p>

<h3 id="building-energy-end-use-charts">3. Building Energy End Use Charts</h3>
<p>
  The following chart shows the breakdown of energy usage by end use:
</p>
<!-- Insert chart here -->

<h3 id="weather-effects-on-energy-use">4. Weather Effects on Energy Use</h3>
<p>
  The building's energy usage is affected by weather conditions, with higher electricity usage during summer months due
  to cooling loads and higher natural gas usage during winter months due to heating loads.
</p>

<h3 id="aggregated-electric-gas-consumption-table">5. Aggregated Electric and Gas Consumption Table</h3>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Month</th>
      <th class="text-right">Electricity (kWh)</th>
      <th class="text-right">Natural Gas (therms)</th>
      <th class="text-right">Total Cost ($)</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {{#each monthlyData.electric}}
    <tr>
      <td>{{this.month}}</td>
      <td class="text-right">{{formatNumber this.usage}}</td>
      <td class="text-right">
        {{#if ../monthlyData.naturalGas}}
        {{formatNumber (lookup (lookup ../monthlyData.naturalGas @index) 'usage')}}
        {{else}}
        N/A
        {{/if}}
      </td>
      <td class="text-right">{{formatCurrency this.cost}}</td>
    </tr>
    {{/each}}
  </tbody>
</table>
